  "prompt": "When a parking sign says 2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday, what does it mean for the remainder of the time?",
  "response": "When a parking sign indicates \"2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday,\" it means that during those hours, you can park for up to 2 hours at a time. Outside of those specified days and times, parking regulations may differ. Typically, for the remainder of the time (nights, weekends, and holidays), parking may be unrestricted or may have different regulations, such as free parking or no time limit. However, it is always advisable to check for additional signs or local parking regulations indicating any restrictions that might apply outside of the specified hours.",
